laboratory_examinations.findings: The examination showed mild bilateral atelectasis with no pleural effusion. The hepatic parenchyma was homogeneous with no focal lesions or biliary ductal dilatation. The pancreas and spleen were normal. Kidneys normal in size and symmetric with no concerning lesions. Numerous diverticula noted, with areas of wall thickening and hyperemia in the sigmoid colon. There were pockets of free air in the peritoneum, but no discrete fluid collection or bowel obstruction.
